                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13469280" author="jgordon" created="Thu, 4 Oct 2012 11:35:19 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to refactor resolvers into 3 cascading chains&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13472642" author="azaroth" created="Tue, 9 Oct 2012 20:10:49 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you regenerate the patch with --no-prefix option and without the email headers?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, can you explain why maven2 is both on internal and external resolver?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Canceling patch for the moment.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13474809" author="jgordon" created="Fri, 12 Oct 2012 06:10:53 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Great eye, thank you!  I think maven2 is in both due to a merge conflict.  Next patch will fix both.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13480921" author="jgordon" created="Sun, 21 Oct 2012 08:50:47 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated to remove prefix and email headers.  Also adding update checks that route down to the fs resolver.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This allows the local mvn cache resolvers to pick up local cross-product changes instead of reading the stale .ivy2 cache.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13480922" author="jgordon" created="Sun, 21 Oct 2012 08:54:25 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Allows cleaner resolution of changes to local builds of dependent projects for cross-project development, and leverages the local .m2 cache by default.  Default resolver is now the kitchen sink resolver that picks up all the rest, in order of locality.  Internal (default .m2 cache), then external.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13482004" author="azaroth" created="Tue, 23 Oct 2012 02:01:41 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;br/&gt;
Committed to trunk.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks John!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13482026" author="jgordon" created="Tue, 23 Oct 2012 02:42:11 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
